  "text": "Did you leave October Prime Day empty-handed? While the sale ended on Oct. 9, several noteworthy deals have lingered, especially on Roku devices. Known for its streaming solutions, Roku also offers various smart home products, including security cameras, smart TVs and light bulbs. If you’re looking to enhance your home or find an early holiday gift, now is a great time to snag these Roku devices before the offers expire.Many of the best Roku devices, from the CNET favorite Roku Express 4K Plus to the Roku Streambar are still listed at reduced rates. These discounted devices also make excellent smart home gifts for the holidays, so now's the time to buy them. Discover the best Prime Day-adjacent Roku deals we've found from Amazon and competing retailers below.Best post-Prime Day Roku deals Streaming sticks can help make streaming your favorite content super simple, especially if you don't have a smart TV. One of our favorite ones is the Roku Express 4K Plus, thanks to its straightforward interface and great value for money. This easy-to-use streaming stick is down to $27 at Amazon, saving you $13. The brand new 2024 Roku Ultra, only recently released, is already discounted by 21% for Prime Day. That's the lowest it's gone since release and a rare chance to save on such a new device.  This Roku smart light A19 bulb is only $8, thanks to a 20% discount. With up to 16 million colors to choose from capable of 1,100 lumens as well as Alexa and Google Home support, this is a bargain. Get a whole 4K TV with Roku's easy-to-use software built right in and save $50 -- No need for additional streaming sticks or boxes.  More post-Prime Day Roku dealsRoku 50-inch 4K TV: $230 (save $70). A 4K HDR TV optimized for room lighting with automatic brightness.Hisense 40-inch Class A4 Series Smart Roku TV: $150 (save $20). This is a 1080p TV with Roku's streaming platform built in, and it is compatible with Amazon Alexa and Google Assistant. Roku smart home wireless video doorbell: $100 (save $14). An HD video doorbell and chime with a six-month battery.Roku outdoor wired security camera: $30 (save $20). It supports 1080p night vision, has two-way audio and is IP65 weather-resistant. Roku smart LED light strip: $40 (save $10). These peel-and-stick Wi-Fi-enabled light strips add a burst of color.Roku smart light bulbs (white, 4-pack): $15 (save $8). These lights can be scheduled or manually adjusted to change brightness and temperature. Roku Express streaming device: $18 (save $12). Nab this simple streaming stick for 40% off.Roku voice remote: $28 (save $3). Life is much easier when you don't have to enter your Netflix password using the remote's keys.Roku indoor camera: $35 (save $7). Achieve peace of mind when you're not home with this 360 camera. A 90-day subscription is also included. Roku Streambar SE: $60 (save $40). Get this Roku soundbar with built-in streaming for a one-stop shop.  Extend Amazon Prime Day Savings With These Shopping Tips See all photos Is Prime Day the best time to buy a Roku device?Yes, Prime Day is one of the best opportunities to snag a Roku device, with prices historically dropping to record lows during the event. If you're in the market for an upgraded streaming stick, Roku-powered soundbar or TV set, the Prime Day sale is usually the time to buy. The sale officially ended on Oct. 9, but some deals have lingered. Once these savings disappear, you may want to hold off on buying until the next major shopping event.  Watch this: How to Hack Amazon Prime Day: Shopping and Deals Advice 04:03Are Roku deals available post-Prime Day? Prime Day is officially over, but some Roku devices are still available. We don't expect these deals to last much longer. If you're looking for one and it's listed above, then it's probably worth going for it.",
